  "body": "***Type***: Bug\r\n\r\n***Summary***: If Android user is log out of state (Status app is closed) and taps on a universal link for public chat, user needs to log in first. In that case contact ends up on infinite 'Signing you in...' screen.\r\n\r\nIt works **fine on iOS**.\r\nEverything is OK if contact logged in to account. Happens only when (s)he need to log in\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nPublic chat is opened from universal link after user logs in to account \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nEndless 'Signing you in...' and no public chat is opened when I login in to account navigated from universal link for public chat\r\n\r\n<img width=\"226\" alt=\"screen shot 2018-09-03 at 15 54 07\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/44987946-a51c1580-af91-11e8-8b8b-8818ed6c3a00.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status and create a new user\r\n- Close Status app\r\n- Open universal link for public chat / Dapp (e.g. https://get.status.im/chat/public/myuniquepubchat)\r\n- You should be redirected to Status login page. \r\n- Log in to your account (entering valid password)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information 1\r\nInfinite `Signing you in...` appear in Develop `0.9.26 (7511); node v0.13.1` \r\n* Operating System: Android 6.0+ 7.0\r\n\r\n### Additional Information 2\r\nIn the nightly build Develop `0.9.26 (7253); node 19b53030` behavior was that I was able to log in but no public chat was opened\r\n* Operating System: Android 6.0+ 7.0\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\nWhen infinite login process https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8578281/sessions/4400328805/?accessToken=5/PLWzIGJACGSKlRdFTJY3PBqGA\r\n\r\n",
